         <div xml:id="header">
            <head type="main">Encoding Correspondence</head>
            <head type="sub">A Manual for Encoding Letters and Postcards in TEI-XML and DTABf</head>
            <p>Edited by Stefan Dumont, Susanne Haaf, and Sabine Seifert</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="content">
            <div n="1">
               <head>Introduction</head>
               <p>Historical correspondence has been digitally edited and published with
                  growing interest for years. This publication is intended to help editors to encode letters
                  and postcards in TEI-XML and DTABf. <ref target="introduction.xml">[Read
                     More]</ref></p>
            </div>
            <div n="2">
               <head>Open Peer Review</head>
               <p>Annotate the articles and give feedback with the Annotation Platform <ref
                  target="https://hypothes.is">Hypothes.is</ref>. Of course you can also contact us via <ref target="mailto:encoding-correspondence@bbaw.de">e-mail</ref>. 
                  We're looking forward to
                  hearing from you!</p>
            </div>
            <div n="3">
               <listBibl>
                  <head>Latest Articles</head>
                  <bibl>
                     <title><ref target="uncertainties-metadata.xml">Uncertainties in metadata</ref></title>
                     <author>Peter Dängeli, Isabella Hödl-Notter, Timo Steyer</author>
                  </bibl>
                  <bibl>
                     <title><ref target="addresses.xml">Addresses</ref></title>
                     <author>Marjam Trautmann</author> 
                  </bibl>
                  <bibl>
                     <title><ref target="stamps-seals-postmarks.xml">Postage stamps, seals, and postmarks</ref></title>
                     <author>Josephine Obert, Marjam Trautmann</author>
                  </bibl>
                  <bibl>
                     <title><ref target="CMIF.xml">Correspondence Metadata Interchange
                        Format</ref></title>
                     <author>Stefan Dumont, Ingo Börne, Jonas Müller-Laackman, Dominik Leipold,
                        Gerlinde Schneider</author>
